HEADWORD: Bitartrate
<hw>Bi*tar"trate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt of tartaric acid in which the base replaces but half the
acid hydrogen; an acid tartrate, as cream of tartar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

